The Grinch was feeling mighty bold,
He locked CECE out, and took control,
Of the KDAY radio station, a feat,
He started playing his favorite beat.
Ain’t Nothing But a G Thang,
Was the jam he played all day,
He sang along with Snoop Dogg’s flow,
As CECE tried to regain control.
But the Grinch was having too much fun,
He refused to let CECE back on,
He kept on rapping and spinning tunes,
Leaving CECE out in the dunes.
But the Queen of Los Angeles, she wouldn’t stay down,
She fought back with all her might and renown,
And in the end, she took back her throne,
The Grinch was forced to leave, all alone.
So CECE is back on the air,
Spinning tunes without a care,
The Grinch has learned his lesson well,
Never mess with CECE, she’ll always prevail.

Today I spoke at the #SouthEastLaWomensConference 🌺 I have to be honest with you…I prayed as I was driving there and asked God to give me the right words to speak… I prayed that HE let me be a vessel for HIM. I heard God say “Stand in your truth” … I cried as I was driving there …it was such an emotional & personal moment for me. I knew there was gonna be young girls there that needed a hug, some advice or just someone to look at them and tell them how amazing & beautiful they are. The 3rd slide & 7th slide means so much to me. After I gave my speech this beautiful little girl came up to me…and she was crying and she hugged me so tight and said “I think God brought you to me, Cece” 😭😭😭
I said “HE did, baby” and I hugged her and sat with her privately and just spoke with her and let her talk to me for as long as she needed. I now know why I was so emotional going there. Everyone there was meant for me to cross paths with but her…that little Angel..she was really why I was there. She needed to hear my words of encouragement, understanding and struggle - to understand that she too can overcome any obstacle. Today I was a messenger for God 🥰🙏🏼♥️ and it felt so beautiful. Never be afraid to share ur story- u never know who needs to hear it. 

Thank you to my amazing tribe for being there for me. I only surround myself with empowered women who legit love to uplift other women. I don’t know what I would do without u amazing women! U really are Superwoman & Wonder Woman all rolled up in one with a whole lotta Dolores Huerta mixed in!! Love u girls for always being there for me! @iamgeorginaavilez @erikajeaneatte @misswendylou 🌺👑🌺👑🌺👑

Dear Sandee,
I got the call the day you passed away…I was driving on the fwy, I lost it 😭. I don’t even know how I got to my destination- thru the tears & the wailing… all I could hear was you say my name over & over again “Cecilia!” … I just kept saying “I love you Sandee” 
You were just 17 yrs old when we met. You came up to me & asked if you could learn radio from me…I was super tough on you & told you I was willing to help train you but the minute you miss a session, I was done because I didn’t want my time wasted. Little did I know you were the most determined person I would meet in Vegas and never missed a session (except for ur finals lol) - I teased you that your were the only person I knew who celebrated their 18th bday at a 21 & over club. You became one of my closest friends and we would go on to have so many crazy moments… a lot that is documented on ur flip camera. You would say “Get ready Cecilia cuz I’m bringing Flip” We would steal the orange combs from the construction sites & create our own VIP parking at the clubs. I would have gatherings at my place & u would say “I’m bringing desserts, cuz girl im not cooking!” I remember one time I hosted a really horrible club & I was mad cuz I didn’t want to do it and you said “Cecilia, go host & get ur money! That money is gonna be for ur dining room table!" You came with me and stood by my side. 
That’s why I had to fly in for ur funeral- I had to say my final goodby to you. It was so fucking hard…you were just radiant 💫💫💫 Anyone who knew you- knew how glamorous & radiant u were. I remember when we came up with ur name …Sandee La Chika Bonita & I remember when u wanted to shorten it & I was like just go w/ Sandee Bonita & we laughed was like duh! So many memories…so many. I remember them all. I’ll always remember u I’ll never forget. Never. We laughed, cried, got into trouble together & had the most fun. I would never imagine that I would be sitting in a pew attending ur funeral. Never. You were life, Sandee. Now you’re eternal. It took me a while to post- I just guess I wasn’t ready to say goodbye. U had a beautiful funeral…all the flowers were pink & white - beautiful like u. #LoveU ♥️🌺🕊️🙏🏼💫
🙏🏼🌺♥️💕 May your strength hold u up today 🙌🏼

social_posts.post_text: Didn’t know what to post or what to say. Right before Thanksgiving my mom had her 7th stroke and on Friday, December 22nd at 12:40 noon my baby Charlie passed away. He was 16 years old. Can’t lie- my heart is broken 😞 but no matter what…I gotta thank God that my mom is still here 🙏🏽 and that he gave me 16 beautiful years with my Charlie. I’m so thankful for @guapcityproductions he has loved me thru all my pain. I love you babe so much. Thank u for the long conversations, the drives and taking me to church when I’m breaking. To my sister @ina_bug I love you sister 🌺 ur my life twin and I’m thankful for you everyday …I couldn’t do this life without u. Blessings come in every form…this year has taught me to really appreciate small moments …cuz they’re the moments that really matter ❤️ I pray all of you have beautiful and more meaningful moments in 2024. May God bless you all!
Embracing a fresh start with a new beginning… feeling refreshed…relaxed…and ready to make the next 365 days count 🤍 🙏🏽 @guapcityproductions life with you is a blessing
